In a press briefing, White House spokesperson Karine Jean-Pierre provided an update on President Biden's activities and highlighted the administration's focus on delivering for the American people. She mentioned the President's recent remarks on cancer research, the passage of the Inflation Reduction Act, and his visit to the Detroit Auto Show. Jean-Pierre also criticized Republicans for engaging in divisive political theater and rolling back rights and benefits. She specifically mentioned their efforts to restrict abortion rights and the actions of Republican governors in transporting asylum seekers to other states as political stunts. Jean-Pierre emphasized the administration's commitment to comprehensive immigration reform and securing the release of American citizens detained in other countries. She also mentioned the upcoming United Nations General Assembly and the President's planned trip to the UK.